<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07993</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REGULATING ELECTRONIC CIGARETTES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Defines among others:  “E-cigarette” (product that can be used for the consumption of a nicotine-containing vapour) “Nicotine” (nicotinic alkaloids, including any salt or complex of nicotine whether derived from tobacco or synthetically produced); “Vaping” (act of using an e-cigarette).
Provides that nicotine containers shall bear a textual health warnings “This product may damage your health and is addictive”; and a retailer signage statement shall likewise be posted:  “SALE/DISTRIBUTION TO OR PURCHASE BY MINORS OF E-CIGARETTES IS UNLAWFUL” or “IT IS UNLAWFUL FOR E-CIGARETTES TO BE SOLD/DISTRIBUTED TO OR PURCHASED BY PERSONS UNDER 18 YEARS OF AGE”.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BARBERS, ROBERT ACE S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-08-16)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2018-08-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON HEALTH</td></tr></table>